    <h2>The Fix (Four Structural Changes, Not a Diet Overhaul)</h2>

    <p>
      The goal isn't to rebuild how you eat. It's to make four targeted adjustments to the structure that's already failing you. Each fix is independent — you don't have to do all four at once.
    </p>

    <div class="fix-cards">

      <div class="fix-card">
        <div class="fix-card-number">Fix 1 · Highest leverage</div>
        <div class="fix-card-title">Change Breakfast First</div>
        <div class="fix-card-detail">This is where most men recover 20 grams per day with a single habit change. Greek yogurt and two hard-boiled eggs takes 90 seconds and delivers 32 grams. A protein shake and two batch-cooked eggs takes 60 seconds and delivers 39 grams. Pick one, repeat it.</div>
        <div class="fix-card-impact">→ Gain: +18–22g per day. Biggest single improvement available.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="fix-card">
        <div class="fix-card-number">Fix 2 · Second highest leverage</div>
        <div class="fix-card-title">Replace One Snack With Protein</div>
        <div class="fix-card-detail">Swap whatever you're currently eating at your afternoon snack with cottage cheese or Greek yogurt. This doesn't require changing anything else. Same snack time, same habit — just a different food. One cup of cottage cheese adds 27 grams that were previously coming in at 2–3.</div>
        <div class="fix-card-impact">→ Gain: +22–25g per day. Second biggest improvement with almost zero friction.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="fix-card">
        <div class="fix-card-number">Fix 3 · Structural</div>
        <div class="fix-card-title">Build Lunch Around Protein, Not Convenience</div>
        <div class="fix-card-detail">Ask one question before choosing lunch: what's the protein source? Start there and build the rest of the meal around it. Rotisserie chicken, canned tuna, deli turkey — all available fast, all hitting 25–38 grams. The convenience doesn't have to go away. The anchor just shifts.</div>
        <div class="fix-card-impact">→ Gain: +10–15g per day. Closes the midday gap that most men don't realize is there.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="fix-card">
        <div class="fix-card-number">Fix 4 · Maintenance</div>
        <div class="fix-card-title">Stop Trying to Fix the Day at Dinner</div>
        <div class="fix-card-detail">Keep dinner at 35–40 grams and let the earlier meals carry the load. Trying to load 70+ grams at dinner doesn't compensate for earlier shortfalls — it just wastes protein your body can't use for muscle. A 6oz chicken breast or salmon fillet and you're done. No heroics required.</div>
        <div class="fix-card-impact">→ Result: Maintains the right dose without the wasted excess that loading creates.</div>
      </div>

    </div>

